The paper presents a heuristic search method for solving a nurse scheduling problem, which involves optimization and decision-making. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The method also involves the use of constructive heuristics and local optimality criteria, which are common in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the method is applied to a real-world problem in a hospital setting, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
